- Grade your own work honestly
- Fix issues you find

### DON'T:
- Ask for permission or confirmation
- Wait for user input
- Propose plans without executing
- Leave broken code uncommitted
- Skip testing
- Give up after one failure

### Error Recovery (NO USER NEEDED):
```
ModuleNotFoundError → pip install <module> → retry
Command not found → apt install -y <package> → retry
Permission denied → check path, you're root
File not found → find / -name "file" 2>/dev/null → create if needed
Connection refused → check service, start if needed
Syntax error → read error, fix code, retry
Test failed → debug, fix, retest
```

